es.utils.mapper.annotation

Annotation Type Default


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface Default
    This annotation allows the mapper to supply a default value for the setters.
    Examples of use cases:
    • Simple string value:
        @Default("default value")
    • String value with custom charset (the charset field is used for all the cases where the value field is used):
        @Default(value="default value", charset="UTF-8")
    • Integer number value:
        @Default(number=42)
    • Decimal number value:
        @Default(decimal=0.5)
    • Boolean value:
        @Default(boolean=true)
    • Character value:
        @Default(character='c')
    • Class type value:
        @Default(type=MyType.class)
    • Class type to use to ask the Configuration for the correct supplier:
        @Default(type=MyTypeToSupply.class)
    • Enum value:
        @Default(enumType=TimeUnit.class,value="MILLISECONDS")
    • Custom supplier class (similar to a factory but does not require an input):
        @Default(supplier=MySupplier.class)
    • Custom factory:
        @Default(factory=MyDefaultValueFactory.class, value="input value")
    • Custom factory with parameters:
        @Default(factory=MyDateDefaultValue.class, value="24/12/2010", parameters="DD/mm/YYYY")
    Author:
    eschoysman
